{"parse":{"title":"Nanny van","pageid":5806125,"revid":844452435,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:NannyVan20060727-DSCN4031.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/de/NannyVan20060727-DSCN4031.jpg/220px-NannyVan20060727-DSCN4031.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"165\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/de/NannyVan20060727-DSCN4031.jpg/330px-NannyVan20060727-DSCN4031.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/de/NannyVan20060727-DSCN4031.jpg/440px-NannyVan20060727-DSCN4031.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"2048\" data-file-height=\"1536\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:NannyVan20060727-DSCN4031.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>A modern <a href=\"/wiki/Nissan_Caravan#E24_(1986\u20132001)\" title=\"Nissan Caravan\">Nissan Urvan</a> nanny van. It is larger than those of the 1980s.</div></div></div>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Toyota_Coaster_School_Bus_2016.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b6/Toyota_Coaster_School_Bus_2016.jpg/220px-Toyota_Coaster_School_Bus_2016.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"165\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b6/Toyota_Coaster_School_Bus_2016.jpg/330px-Toyota_Coaster_School_Bus_2016.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b6/Toyota_Coaster_School_Bus_2016.jpg/440px-Toyota_Coaster_School_Bus_2016.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"2816\" data-file-height=\"2112\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Toyota_Coaster_School_Bus_2016.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><a href=\"/wiki/Toyota_Coaster\" title=\"Toyota Coaster\">Toyota Coaster</a> School Private Light Bus in 2016</div></div></div>\n<p>The <b>Nanny Van</b> (<a href=\"/wiki/Traditional_Chinese_characters\" title=\"Traditional Chinese characters\">Chinese</a>&#58; <span lang=\"zh-Hant\">\u8913\u59c6\u8eca</span>) or <b>School Private Light Bus</b> is a kind of <a href=\"/wiki/School_bus\" title=\"School bus\">school bus</a> service in <a href=\"/wiki/Hong_Kong\" title=\"Hong Kong\">Hong Kong</a>. At its peak of popularity during the 1980s, it had become a form of \"illegal\" <a href=\"/wiki/Public_transportation\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Public transportation\">public transportation</a>. Subsequently, due to unauthorized use of the vans, the <a href=\"/wiki/Government_of_Hong_Kong\" title=\"Government of Hong Kong\">government</a> banned them as a form of public transportation and required all existing nanny vans to register and operate on designated routes.\n</p><p>All nanny vans in service today are required by the government to have both the Chinese text \"\u5b78\u6821\u79c1\u5bb6\u5c0f\u5df4\" and the English text \"SCHOOL PRIVATE LIGHT BUS\" in <a href=\"/wiki/Capital_letter\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Capital letter\">capital letters</a> painted on the sides of the vans. There were 1769 such buses registered with the <a href=\"/wiki/Transport_Department\" title=\"Transport Department\">Transport Department</a> in 2014.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Provision_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Provision-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Regulated_service\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Regulated service</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#See_also\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">See also</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#External_links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External links</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Nanny_van&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: History\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Nanny vans were originally a <a href=\"/wiki/Minivan\" title=\"Minivan\">small van</a> operated in Hong Kong to ferry <a href=\"/wiki/Pre-school\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Pre-school\">pre-school</a> children from their homes to their nurseries and kindergartens. Most of these vans were run by private agreement between the schools and the drivers. These original nanny vans seated four to five adults; other seats in the van were removed and replaced with a narrow sofa around the cabin. With such an arrangement, the van could transport 10-12 children.\n</p><p>During the 1980s, when living standards in Hong Kong were rising, some drivers wanted to earn extra income with their vans. Therefore, when it was time for secondary schools to have their lunch break, the vans started to transport the younger children back to school. Each student paid about $1\u2013$2, which was about half the price for them to share a taxi. Most of these vans served <a href=\"/wiki/North_Point\" title=\"North Point\">North Point</a>, where they either stopped at the <a href=\"/wiki/North_Point_Pier\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"North Point Pier\">North Point Pier</a> or under <a href=\"/wiki/Fortress_Hill\" title=\"Fortress Hill\">Fortress Hill</a>. They picked up school children until all the seats were occupied and traveled along the Cloud View Road, making stops at each school.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Regulated_service\">Regulated service</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Nanny_van&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Regulated service\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>In the early 1990s, there was an <a href=\"/wiki/Traffic_collision\" title=\"Traffic collision\">accident</a> in North Point involving a nanny van and its passengers were injured. The accident exposed the illegal service and the government issued a ban and required all nanny vans to run only along designated routes.\n</p><p>Nanny vans are still available in Hong Kong. Many schools are able to afford their own vans. Less affluent schools continue to sign agreements with van drivers. These drivers provide school bus services for the more remote areas of Hong Kong, transporting school children from rural villages to schools in urban areas. The nanny vans have grown to the size of a mini bus.\n</p><p>School private light buses are one of three legal classified vehicles for transport of schoolchildren. The other two are non-franchised public buses and private buses operated by schools directly.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Provision_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Provision-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>There were similar services introduced  also elsewhere, for example in <a href=\"/wiki/Richmond,_Virginia\" title=\"Richmond, Virginia\">Richmond, Virginia</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-VA1_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-VA1-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Nanny_van&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Marshrutka\" title=\"Marshrutka\">Marshrutka</a>, an equivalent mode of transportation in some ex-<a href=\"/wiki/Soviet_Bloc\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Soviet Bloc\">Soviet Bloc</a> countries</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Nanny_van&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Provision-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-Provision_1-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-Provision_1-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.info.gov.hk/gia/general/201407/02/P201407021871.htm\">\"LCQ6: Provision of school bus services.\"</a> <a href=\"/wiki/Gary_Chan\" title=\"Gary Chan\">Chan Hak-kan</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Anthony_Cheung\" title=\"Anthony Cheung\">Anthony Cheung Bing-leung</a>. <i>Press Releases.</i> <a href=\"/wiki/Government_of_Hong_Kong\" title=\"Government of Hong Kong\">Government</a>. 2 July 2014. Retrieved 2017-06-12. </span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-VA1-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-VA1_2-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://sitter.com/nanny-van-llc-child-care-richmond-va-2\">\"Shakeya Key, Nanny Van\"</a><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">18 November</span> 2017</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Shakeya+Key%2C+Nanny+Van&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fsitter.com%2Fnanny-van-llc-child-care-richmond-va-2&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ANanny+van\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_links\">External links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Nanny_van&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: External links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.info.gov.hk/gia/general/200304/01/0401145.htm\">Request from Hong Kong Government for Nanny Van owners to keep their vans clean during the SARS outbreak</a></li></ul>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nParsed by mw1246\nCached time: 20180909064139\nCache expiry: 1900800\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.072 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.103 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 151/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 0/1500000\nPost\u2010expand include size: 1725/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 73/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 7/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/500\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post\u2010expand size: 1638/5000000 bytes\nNumber of Wikibase entities loaded: 0/400\nLua time usage: 0.024/10.000 seconds\nLua memory usage: 1.32 MB/50 MB\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%   72.465      1 -total\n 64.64%   46.839      1 Template:Reflist\n 47.46%   34.392      1 Template:Cite_web\n 31.25%   22.648      1 Template:Zh\n  3.22%    2.335      1 Template:Main_other\n-->\n\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key enwiki:pcache:idhash:58061